<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Phylogram of Rhytismataceae is presented as the best tree revealed by MP analysis, based on the concatenated LSU-ITS-mtSSU sequence dataset. MP bootstrap support values (MPBP ≥ 50 %) and Bayesian inference posterior probabilities (BYPP ≥ 0.95) are shown near the nodes. The tree is rooted to Marthamyces emarginatus (ICMP 22854), the scale bar showing 10 changes. Type strains are indicated in bold and new sequences, generated in this study, are given in red." , "Figure 2. Hypoderma paralinderae a, b apothecia observed under a dissecting microscope in face view c vertical section through an apothecium d lips adjacent to the top of covering stroma e section of covering stroma f section of basal stroma g paraphyses and asci in various states of maturity h immature ascus i, j ascospores. Note: c-j mounted in water. Scale bar: 1 mm (a), 500 µm (b), 200 µm (c), 20 µm (d, g, h), 10 µm (e, i, j), 5 µm (f)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/492862" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/492863" .

